30|$|After {{the cooling}} {{phase of the}} castings, the {{shake-out}} and take-out stage allows to get the casting separated by the moulding box and the sand. In this phase, the <b>circulating</b> <b>scrap</b> and the sand are recovered to be re-used in the production process. Finally, the finishing phase includes the shot blasting (necessary to eliminate the remaining sand), the deburring (can be automatic or manual) and, eventually, the painting.|$|E

